## Tool Validation Requirements

**CRITICAL**: Always validate recommended tools before use to prevent governance failures:

| Tool | Validation Command | Expected Result |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Lint batched script | `./scripts/lint-batched.sh --docs-only --dry-run` | Dry run completes without errors |
| Exit code check | `echo "Exit code: $?"` | Should be 0 for successful validation |
| SHA capture | `./scripts/capture-sha.sh --help 2>/dev/null \|\| echo "missing"` | Shows help or reports missing |

**Pre-execution Checklist**:

- [ ]  Verify script exists and is executable
- [ ]  Check exit code behavior matches expectations
- [ ]  Confirm no false positives in output
- [ ]  Test dry-run mode when available

Never assume recommended tools work correctly without validation. Tool failures can cause session governance violations.

