## SDD/TDD Coordination Patterns

**Integration Points**: Session managers must understand how to coordinate Spec-Driven Development and Test-Driven Development workflows.

### SDD Phase Transitions

| SDD Phase | Session Manager Role | TDD Integration | Success Criteria |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **Specify** (`/specify`) | Define testable acceptance criteria | Generate test requirements | Clear, measurable outcomes |
| **Plan** (`/plan`) | Coordinate architectural decisions | Design test strategy | Technical approach approved |
| **Tasks** (`/tasks`) | Create dependency-ordered implementation | Map tasks to test phases | Ready for execution |
| **Implement** (`/implement`) | Monitor TDD Guard enforcement | Ensure failing tests exist first | Working code + passing tests |

### TDD Guard Integration Workflow

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    Specify["/specify requirements"] --> Plan["/plan architecture"]
    Plan --> Tasks["/tasks breakdown"]
    Tasks --> TestGen[Generate failing tests]
    TestGen --> Guard{TDD Guard}
    Guard -->|✅ Tests exist| Implement["/implement feature"]
    Guard -->|❌ No tests| Block[Block implementation]
    Block --> WriteTests[Write failing tests]
    WriteTests --> Guard
    Implement --> Verify[Verify tests pass]
    Verify --> Review[Code review + logic check]

```

### Session Orchestration for SDD/TDD

**Phase 1: Specification & Planning**

- Session manager coordinates `/specify` and `/plan` phases
- Ensures acceptance criteria are testable
- Sets up test strategy and coverage requirements
- Creates handoff protocols between specification and implementation

**Phase 2: Test-First Implementation**

- Coordinates TDD Guard setup and enforcement
- Monitors test creation before implementation
- Ensures proper red-green-refactor cycle adherence
- Handles escalations when TDD violations occur

**Phase 3: Quality & Integration**

- Coordinates code review with test validation
- Ensures implementation meets original specifications
- Manages handoff to deployment/integration teams
- Updates governance trackers with outcomes

### SDD/TDD Escalation Protocols

| Issue Type | Session Manager Action | Escalation Path | Resolution |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| **TDD Guard blocks implementation** | Verify failing tests exist | Guide test creation process | Unblock implementation |
| **Specification ambiguity** | Coordinate `/clarify` session | Route to product stakeholders | Updated specifications |
| **Test strategy conflicts** | Facilitate architecture review | Convene technical stakeholders | Agreed test approach |
| **Implementation deviates from spec** | Trigger specification review | Product + engineering alignment | Specification or code update |

